PPMJoyStick is an ultra-simple, highly-configurable virtual joystick interface for flight simulators.

This software is intended for use with fpv radio controllers and simulators, however it can be configured and tuned to aviation simulators.


* Supports PPM input via audio jack or sound card

* Maps radio channels to virtual joystick axes and switches

* Real-time plotting for debugging and calibration

* Customizable channel assignments and ranges

* Lightweight script


Flags:

--debug : Show the oscilloscope response
--raw : Print the raw frames and mapped values